The first busload of illegal immigrants sent by Governor Greg Abbott of Texas arrived in New York City in early August.

According to a statement released by the office of the Governor of Texas over the summer, the first bus carrying roughly 50 immigrants from Venezuela, Ecuador, Honduras, and Colombia arrived at the Port Authority Bus Terminal.

‚ÄúThe 1st bus of migrants has arrived in NYC,‚Äù Governor Abbott announced.

‚ÄúBecause of President Biden‚Äôs continued refusal to acknowledge the crisis caused by his open border policies, the State of Texas has had to take unprecedented action to keep our communities safe,‚Äù said Governor Abbott in a statement.

NYC Mayor Eric Adams called Gov. Abbott and Arizona‚Äôs Governor Doug Ducey ‚Äúcowards‚Äù for turning away refugees.
